I need a designer who can make everything from scratch as I have just the idea in my mind. So you're should be the expert I can rely on. 
The deliverables are:
- Mind map;
- Mood board;
- Initial wireframes;
- UI design;
- Styliguide.
As you can see, this job is not about just making UI for the screens/pages but I'm looking for the  well-considered process to turn my idea into prototype I can develop later.
You're welcome to put your best design works in your cover letter.

We are looking for a specialist who will design a website for an employment company in Poland. 
Terms of reference for creating a WDNL (Work Department NL) website design

General requirements:
1. Color scheme: Blue and white, professional, trustworthy;
2. Style: Modern, spacious, easy to read.

Language support and platform:
1. Languages - Polish, English, Russian;
2. Design for PC and Phone - Adapted to both platforms.

Font: 
1. Fonts - Roboto or Open Sans (a combination is possible).

Layout:
We made a layout in the Figma program - this is an example of how the elements of the site and its design should look like.

Notes:
1. The "For Partners" page in the Polish version must be in English;
2. Icons and images can be completely replaced or changed;
3. Only high-quality images and icons of the same style;
4. The page indicated by the "red arrow" is the best design that we managed to achieve on our own;
5. The "portfolio" element will contain videos and photos. Clear and beautiful design.

General requirement:
1. Design - We expect to receive a modified, improved version of the site;
2. The elements of the site need to be animated (made interactive), however, without overloading the perception of information.;
3. Wishes - It is desirable to develop a design in the Figma program.

